	<header class="entry-header">
		<h1 class="entry-title">The Base Design</h1>
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>The base serves three essential purposes. </p>
<li>It supports the rest of the scanner.
</li>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Base_DSC08869.jpg"><img src="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Base_DSC08869-1024x682.jpg" alt="Base_DSC08869" width="730" height="486" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-121" srcset="https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Base_DSC08869-1024x682.jpg 1024w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Base_DSC08869-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Base_DSC08869-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.diybookscanner.org/archivist/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Base_DSC08869-1200x800.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px" /></a></p>
<li>It lifts the book up to the glass of the imaging module.
</li>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ArchivistLift.gif"><img src="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ArchivistLift.gif" alt="ArchivistLift" width="730" height="488" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-785" /></a></p>
<li>It allows the cradle to move side-to-side to accommodate the movement of the center of the book.
</li>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/output_7JG3EW.gif"><img src="wp-content/uploads/2015/03/output_7JG3EW.gif" alt="output_7JG3EW" width="730" height="408" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-789" /></a></p>
			</div><!-- .entry-content -->
